;THE HUMAN P53 PROTEIN USED HAS BEEN ENGINEERED TO ENHANCE ITS THERMAL STABILITY, 
HAS A DELETION IN THE LINKER BETWEEN THE DNA BINDING AND OLIGOMERIZATION DOMAINS AND 
FINALLY TWO AMINO ACID SUBSTITUTIONS THAT CONVERT THE TETRAMERIZATION DOMAIN INTO A DIMERIZATION DOMAIN. 
THE PROTEIN WAS DESCRIBED IN:
PETTY TJ, EMAMZADAH S, COSTANTINO L, PETKOVA I, STAVRIDI ES, SAVEN JG, VAUTHEY E, HALAZONETIS TD. 
AN INDUCED FIT MECHANISM REGULATES P53 DNA BINDING KINETICS TO CONFER SEQUENCE SPECIFICITY. 
EMBO J 30: 2167-76, 2011. ID:21522129
;
